{% style %}
@import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Cormorant+Garamond:ital,wght@0,300;0,400;1,300;1,400&family=Inter:wght@300;400;500&family=IBM+Plex+Mono:wght@300;400&display=swap');
{% endstyle %}

<div class="plekify-v8-fw">

<!-- ═══ SECTION 9: WHY SHOPIFY ═════════════════════════════ -->
<section id="platform" class="v8-band">
  <div class="v8-contain">
    <span class="v8-annot">Why the platform choice is a business decision</span>
    <h2 class="v8-sh">Most travel brands are building<br><em>on the wrong foundation.</em></h2>
    <p class="v8-body v8-prose" style="margin-top:.5rem">OTAs dominate AI-assistant discovery today because they hold structured, queryable inventory. Shopify Catalog MCP and UCP give independent operators the same discoverability — without the commission, and without ceding the customer relationship.</p>
    <p class="v8-body v8-prose" style="margin-top:.5rem;margin-bottom:1.5rem">WordPress and custom sites display a property. They do not compound. Shopify is the infrastructure layer that turns a travel website into a revenue engine — with native commerce intelligence, AI-era discoverability, and an ecosystem that grows with the business.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="v8-contain--wide">
    <table class="v8-comp">
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Capability</th><th>Shopify via Plekify</th><th>WordPress + booking plugin</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Checkout ownership</td><td class="v8-comp--g">100% on your domain. PCI DSS Level 1. 99.99% uptime (Plus).</td><td class="v8-comp--d">Typically redirects to a third-party engine</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Guest data &amp; CRM</td><td class="v8-comp--g">Every booking builds a Shopify customer profile — owned, segmentable, marketable</td><td class="v8-comp--d">Records split across PMS, plugin, and gateway</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Remarketing</td><td class="v8-comp--g">Shopify Email, abandoned checkout recovery, dynamic segments, Flow automations — all native</td><td class="v8-comp--d">External CRM required; PMS data rarely flows to email tools</td></tr>
        <tr><td>AI discoverability</td><td class="v8-comp--g">Shopify Catalog MCP — inventory queryable by ChatGPT, Perplexity, Google AI agents</td><td class="v8-comp--d">No structured agentic discovery layer</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Agentic commerce</td><td class="v8-comp--g">Universal Commerce Protocol (UCP) — supports AI-led booking flows end to end</td><td class="v8-comp--d">No equivalent; dependent on OTAs</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Payment flexibility</td><td class="v8-comp--g">Deposits, instalments, milestone billing, B2B terms, 130+ currencies, Shop Pay</td><td class="v8-comp--d">Plugin-dependent; typically single-payment flows</td></tr>
        <tr><td>International selling</td><td class="v8-comp--g">Shopify Markets — localised pricing, 20+ languages, 130+ currencies, hreflang natively</td><td class="v8-comp--d">Plugin-dependent; hreflang requires dev work</td></tr>
        <tr><td>SEO</td><td class="v8-comp--g">Itineraries rank on your domain — full HTML, automatic sitemaps, structured data</td><td class="v8-comp--d">Wetu itineraries on wetu.com; no SEO value flows to operator</td></tr>
        <tr class="v8-comp__row--highlight"><td>B2B &amp; trade channel</td><td class="v8-comp--g"><strong>Agent pricing tiers, trade catalogues, and negotiated terms — built into Plekify on standard Shopify</strong></td><td class="v8-comp--d">Separate systems required</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Ecosystem</td><td class="v8-comp--g">16 000+ managed apps — no version conflicts, no security patches, no broken upgrades</td><td class="v8-comp--d">Plugin stacks accumulate compatibility risk</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ═══ DIRECT CHANNEL ════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section class="v8-band v8-band--alt">
  <div class="v8-contain">
    <div class="v8-2col">
      <div>
        <span class="v8-annot">The long-term case</span>
        <h2 class="v8-sh">The direct channel is the<br><em>most profitable one you own.</em></h2>
        <p class="v8-body" style="margin-top:.5rem">Booking.com and Airbnb are traffic sources, not competitors. Properties that underinvest in their own website because it generates little direct business have confused cause with effect. The direct channel is underdeveloped because the technology has never matched what OTAs deliver. Plekify changes that equation.</p>
        <p class="v8-body" style="margin-top:.65rem">The direct channel is the only one that simultaneously offers full margin, owned guest data, a controlled brand experience, and the compounding returns of a real CRM.</p>
        <p class="v8-body" style="margin-top:.65rem">The path from a natural-language travel query to a completed booking is becoming automated. Operators on Shopify are in that flow. Operators on custom sites are not.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <span class="v8-annot" style="margin-top:.1rem">What compounds with every direct booking</span>
        <div class="v8-acc"><span class="v8-acc__text">Guest profiles build — email, stay history, spend, preferences</span><span class="v8-acc__plus">+</span></div>
        <div class="v8-acc"><span class="v8-acc__text">Remarketing becomes possible — seasonal offers, loyalty, return stays</span><span class="v8-acc__plus">+</span></div>
        <div class="v8-acc"><span class="v8-acc__text">Abandoned booking recovery — automated, no third-party tool required</span><span class="v8-acc__plus">+</span></div>
        <div class="v8-acc"><span class="v8-acc__text">B2B agent channel — trade pricing and catalogues on one platform</span><span class="v8-acc__plus">+</span></div>
        <div class="v8-acc"><span class="v8-acc__text">AI discoverability — inventory visible to agents, not just crawlers</span><span class="v8-acc__plus">+</span></div>
        <div class="v8-acc"><span class="v8-acc__text">Platform grows with the business — 16 000+ apps, no replatforming</span><span class="v8-acc__plus">+</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ═══ SECTION 10: CONNECTED SYSTEMS ═════════════════════ -->
<section class="v8-band">
  <div class="v8-contain">
    <span class="v8-annot">Connected systems</span>
    <h2 class="v8-sh">Existing operations.<br><em>Connected, not replaced.</em></h2>
    <p class="v8-body v8-prose" style="margin-top:.4rem">Plekify connects to systems already in use and adds what those systems cannot provide: an AI design layer and a direct commerce layer on the operator's own domain.</p>
    <div class="v8-int-grid">
      <div class="v8-int">
        <span class="v8-int__status v8-int__status--live">Live</span>
        <div class="v8-int__name">Wetu</div>
        <p class="v8-body">Full property, room, activity, restaurant, spa, and itinerary synchronisation. PinID and UUID sync. Round-trip — AI designs or enhances, uploads to Wetu, syncs to Shopify.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="v8-int">
        <span class="v8-int__status v8-int__status--live">Live</span>
        <div class="v8-int__name">ResRequest</div>
        <p class="v8-body">Live availability, real-time pricing, provisional reservations, and booking confirmation on payment. 400+ properties across 14 African countries.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="v8-int">
        <span class="v8-int__status v8-int__status--soon">Roadmap</span>
        <div class="v8-int__name">NightsBridge</div>
        <p class="v8-body">Integration roadmap. Same architecture — live availability, real-time pricing, on-domain checkout with reservation created in the PMS automatically.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="v8-int">
        <span class="v8-int__status v8-int__status--soon">Roadmap</span>
        <div class="v8-int__name">Tourplan</div>
        <p class="v8-body">The central reservations and back-office system used collectively by TSC consortium members. Tourplan and Travelogic run the operational backbone — quoting, costing, supplier management, and invoicing. Plekify does not replace or duplicate that infrastructure. It adds a direct commerce layer on the operator's own domain that Tourplan was never designed to provide.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="v8-body v8-sm" style="margin-top:1rem">The architecture connects to any system with an open API. Some operators — including those running proprietary in-house quoting and reservations systems — require custom integration paths. The API-first design accommodates these without architectural changes.</p>
    <div class="v8-hl" style="margin-top:1.25rem">
      <p class="v8-body"><strong class="v8-hl__label">Merchant-of-record flexibility:</strong> Plekify's architecture supports multiple commercial configurations. The property, the operator, or an existing payment intermediary can serve as the merchant of record — the entity that processes the transaction and receives guest payments. The right configuration depends on the operator's existing agreements and commercial structure. Every model uses the same Shopify checkout infrastructure.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ═══ SECTION 11: THE FOUNDER ═══════════════════════════ -->
<section id="builder" class="v8-band v8-band--alt">
  <div class="v8-contain">
    <span class="v8-annot">The builder</span>
    <div class="v8-builder">
      <div>
        <div class="v8-builder__profile">
          <img class="v8-builder__avatar" src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0582/6776/2747/files/matthew-swart.jpg?v=1773736621" alt="Matthew Swart" loading="lazy">
          <div>
            <div class="v8-builder__name">Matthew Swart</div>
            <div class="v8-builder__role">Founder, Plekify</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <h2 class="v8-sh">25 years building<br><em>African travel technology.</em></h2>
        <p class="v8-body" style="margin-top:.6rem">In 1999 he co-founded SafariNow.com — which grew over 18 years to R320 million in annual booking value, 150 employees, and a 2017 exit to TravelStart. The company raised four rounds of funding, from a South African angel investor through London's First Tuesday network to <a class="v8-text-link" href="https://www.tigerglobal.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Tiger Global</a> in New York — institutional capital that validated the thesis that African travel technology could scale globally.</p>
        <p class="v8-body" style="margin-top:.6rem">The problems Plekify solves are the ones that emerged from building and operating inside the industry across those two and a half decades. Every implementation is set up directly with Matthew — no account managers, no handoffs, no support queue.</p>
        <p class="v8-body" style="margin-top:.6rem"><a class="v8-text-link" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20260109235108/https://www.safarinow.com/cms/matthew-swart" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Read Matthew's SafariNow journey ↗</a></p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <span class="v8-annot">Selected background</span>
        <div class="v8-stat"><strong>1999</strong> — Co-founded SafariNow.com</div>
        <div class="v8-stat"><strong>18 years</strong> as CEO — seed to exit</div>
        <div class="v8-stat"><strong>4 funding rounds</strong> — SA angel, London incubator, and institutional capital including <a class="v8-text-link" href="https://www.tigerglobal.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Tiger Global</a> (New York)</div>
        <div class="v8-stat"><strong>R320m</strong> annual booking value at exit</div>
        <div class="v8-stat"><strong>150</strong> employees at peak</div>
        <div class="v8-stat"><strong>2017</strong> — Sold to TravelStart</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ═══ SECTION 12: TWO COMMERCIAL MODELS ═════════════════ -->
<section class="v8-band">
  <div class="v8-contain">
    <span class="v8-annot">Two ways to start · You are the merchant of record in both</span>
    <h2 class="v8-sh">Choose the model that<br><em>fits how you operate.</em></h2>
    <p class="v8-body v8-prose" style="margin-top:.5rem;margin-bottom:1.25rem">In both models, you are the merchant of record. A Shopify store is registered under your business entity — you configure Shopify Payments, receive payouts directly, and own the customer relationship end to end. Shopify's architecture makes the store owner the merchant of record by default. That is you, not Plekify.</p>
    <div class="v8-price-grid">
      <div class="v8-price v8-price--feat">
        <div class="v8-price__type">Commission model</div>
        <div class="v8-price__name">Zero upfront cost</div>
        <p class="v8-body" style="margin-top:.4rem">Your existing website stays exactly as it is. Plekify lists and presents your products on plekify.com. When a guest is ready to pay, they are passed through to a Shopify checkout registered under your business — you process the payment, you own the guest data.</p>
        <div class="v8-price__highlights">
          <div class="v8-price__highlight-item">Your existing website is unchanged</div>
          <div class="v8-price__highlight-item">You are the merchant of record — payouts go directly to your account</div>
          <div class="v8-price__highlight-item">No Shopify storefront to build or maintain</div>
        </div>
        <ul class="v8-price__list">
          <li>Existing Wetu setup unchanged</li>
          <li>Plekify handles the storefront, you handle the checkout</li>
          <li>Commission on completed transactions only</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="v8-price__note">Test without commitment — keep the customer relationship.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="v8-price">
        <div class="v8-price__type">SaaS model</div>
        <div class="v8-price__name">Your store, our engine</div>
        <p class="v8-body" style="margin-top:.4rem">Plekify is installed on your Shopify store. Your brand, your domain, your customer data. You replace your existing website with a Shopify storefront powered by Plekify — or run it alongside.</p>
        <ul class="v8-price__list">
          <li>You are the merchant of record</li>
          <li>Full Shopify storefront on your domain</li>
          <li>Shopify Payments under your business entity</li>
          <li>Full admin access and first-party data</li>
          <li>Implementation fee + monthly subscription</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="v8-price__note">Full control from day one.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="v8-hl" style="margin-top:1.25rem">
      <p class="v8-body"><strong class="v8-hl__label">Why merchant of record matters:</strong> When a third-party booking engine processes the payment, they are the merchant of record — they hold the guest's payment details, control the checkout experience, and mediate the financial relationship. In both Plekify models, a Shopify store registered under your business processes every transaction. Guest data, payment history, and the commercial relationship belong to you from the first booking. In the commission model, the only Shopify infrastructure you need is the checkout — no storefront, no theme, no store management.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="v8-hl" style="margin-top:1.25rem">
      <p class="v8-body"><strong class="v8-hl__label">Consortium and multi-operator adoption:</strong> For a group of operators sharing a common Wetu and Tourplan stack, rollout is coordinated but never centralised. Each member gets their own Shopify storefront, their own domain, their own guest data, and their own merchant-of-record configuration. There is no shared instance, no pooled data, and no dependency between one operator's store and another's. Implementation is done directly with Matthew — one operator at a time, sequenced to the group's readiness — so that the consortium moves together without any member being forced to wait or rush.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ═══ SECTION 13: CTA ═══════════════════════════════════ -->
<div id="contact" class="v8-band v8-band--cta">
  <div class="v8-contain" style="text-align:center">
    <span class="v8-annot" style="text-align:center">Custom distribution · Get in touch</span>
    <h2 class="v8-sh" style="margin-top:.6rem;text-align:center">Connect your existing operations.<br><em>Nothing needs to change to begin.</em></h2>
    <p class="v8-body" style="margin:0.75rem auto 0;text-align:center;max-width:480px;font-size:12.5px">Existing Wetu content, PMS connections, and OTA channels continue without disruption. The AI design pipeline and a direct commerce layer are added to what is already there.</p>
    <div style="text-align:center">
      <a class="v8-cta__btn" href="mailto:matt@plekify.com">Talk to Matthew ↗</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

